article_title: Bill would reverse some Medicaid cuts, restrictions

article_metadata.description: Adult dental services that were cut from the state’s Medicaid program two years ago would be restored under a bill approved by an Illinois House committee Tuesday.If, in fact, it sticks, it would be great, said Barbara Dunn, interim chief executive officer of Springfield’s Central Counties Health Centers, which provides medical and dental services to low-income patients.The bill, which has the support of Gov. Pat Quinn’s administration, also would exempt Medicaid
article_metadata.author: Dean Olsen Staff Writer
